<!-- Architecture classification report template (Jinja2 syntax).
     Length guide: the entire report should fit on ~1 printed page.
     Rationales are 2-3 sentences max. Evidence is terse file paths, not prose. -->
---
project: "{{ project_name }}"
date: {{ date }}
scope: {{ scope }}
use-type: {{ use_type }}
primary-language: {{ primary_language }}
confidence: {{ confidence }}
styles:
{%- for style in styles %}
  - name: {{ style.name }}
    role: {{ style.role }}
    confidence: {{ style.confidence }}
{%- endfor %}
---

# Architecture Analysis: {{ project_name }}

| | |
|---|---|
| **Scope** | {{ scope }} |
| **Use-type** | {{ use_type }} |
| **Language** | {{ primary_language }} |
| **Confidence** | {{ confidence }} |
{% if repo_url %}| **Repository** | {{ repo_url }} |{% endif %}

## Styles
{# Each rationale: 2-3 sentences. Lead with the structural pattern, cite 1-2 key files, done. #}
{% for style in styles %}
### {{ style.name }} ({{ style.role }})

{{ style.rationale }}
{% endfor %}

## Evidence

{# Key Evidence column: comma-separated file paths or short phrases. No prose. #}
| Style | Confidence | Key Evidence |
|-------|-----------|-------------|
{%- for style in styles %}
| {{ style.name }} | {{ style.confidence }} | {{ style.key_evidence }} |
{%- endfor %}

## Quality Attributes

{# One line per QA. Format: "Name: file1, file2, brief note" — no full sentences. #}
{% for qa in quality_attributes %}
- **{{ qa.name }}**: {{ qa.evidence }}
{%- endfor %}

> Performance, Security, and Testability are architecturally significant but invisible in source code analysis.

## Domain

{{ domain }}{% if domain_justification %} — {{ domain_justification }}{% endif %}

## Production Context

{# 2-4 bullet points. Each bullet: one fact with a number. #}
{% for note in production_context %}
- {{ note }}
{%- endfor %}
